items.title: Cubs overwhelm Mets, maintain Central lead
items.summary: Willson Contreras drove in three runs and had an adventurous night, Javier Baez smacked a solo home run among four hits and Albert Almora Jr. -- who entered the game in the seventh -- drove in a career-high six runs to back Jon Lester and spark the Cubs to a 17-5 victory Wednesday over the Mets at Wrigley Field.
items.content: Willson Contreras drove in three runs and had an adventurous night, Javier Baez smacked a solo home run among four hits and Albert Almora Jr. -- who entered the game in the seventh -- drove in a career-high six runs to back Jon Lester and spark the Cubs to a 17-5 victory Wednesday over the Mets at Wrigley Field.

items.title: Crew backs Chase on short rest to beat Bucs
items.summary: Life without Jimmy Nelson began for the Brewers on Wednesday, when Chase Anderson pitching on short rest in a win.

items.title: Giants pay tribute to former skipper Robinson
items.summary: The Giants highlighted their annual African-American Heritage Night promotion Wednesday by honoring their first black manager, Hall of Fame slugger Frank Robinson, who was responsible for changing the clubhouse culture during his brief but eventful San Francisco tenure.

items.title: Resilient Stroman shakes off tough-luck loss
items.summary: Marcus Stroman still isn't completely over a right arm injury that plagued him earlier this month but it's not going to impact his quest for 200 innings.
